[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] You must have `mpc` installed on your computer in order to use this function.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] clerk is a simple MPD client using rofi or fzf.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] You must have `jq` installed on your computer in order to use this function.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] When you have defined an alias or wrapper for some command, you might want to inherit the completion from a parent function.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] See also `_fzf_setup_completion` in the completion source code.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] Search through your LastPass vault with LastPass CLI and copy password to clipboard.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] FZF will match the query against any text found on the first page of the PDF.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] For instance, one can query for author names, article title, journal, institutions, keywords.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] It works by extracting the text on the first page of the PDF using `pdftotext`.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] The selected file is then opened by the default pdf viewer.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] Requires the pdftotext command line tool.
[src:fzf/fzf-examples-p02] Search records in BibTeX files using FZF, select records to cite, or pretty print in markdown.
