[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] With **--track**, fzf extracts the tracking key from the current item using the nth expression and searches for a matching item in the reloaded list.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] While searching, the UI is blocked (query input and cursor movement are disabled, and the prompt is dimmed).
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] With **reload**, the blocked state clears as soon as the match is found in the stream.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] With **reload-sync**, the blocked state persists until the entire stream is complete.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] Press **Escape** or **Ctrl-C** to cancel the blocked state without quitting fzf.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] The info line shows **+T*** (or **+t*** for one-off tracking) while the search is in progress.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] With **--multi**, selected items are preserved across **reload-sync** by matching their identity fields in the reloaded list.
