[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] fzf exports **$FZF_PREVIEW_LINES** and **$FZF_PREVIEW_COLUMNS** so that they represent the exact size of the preview window.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] fzf also exports **$FZF_PREVIEW_TOP** and **$FZF_PREVIEW_LEFT** so that the preview command can determine the position of the preview window.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] A placeholder expression starting with **+** flag will be replaced to the space-separated list of the selected items (or the current item if no selection was made) individually quoted.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] Similarly, a placeholder expression starting with ***** flag will be replaced to the space-separated list of all matched items individually quoted.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] Each expression expands to a quoted string, so that it's safe to pass it as an argument to an external command.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] So you should not manually add quotes around the curly braces.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] But if you don't want this behavior, you can put **r** flag (raw) in the expression (e.g.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] Use it with caution as unquoted output can lead to broken commands.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] When using a field index expression, leading and trailing whitespace is stripped from the replacement string.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] To preserve the whitespace, use the **s** flag.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] A placeholder expression with **f** flag is replaced to the path of a temporary file that holds the evaluated list.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] This is useful when you pass a large number of items and the length of the evaluated string may exceed **ARG_MAX**.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] Note that you can escape a placeholder pattern by prepending a backslash.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p01] Preview window will be updated even when there is no match for the current query if any of the placeholder expressions evaluates to a non-empty string or **{q}** is in the command template.
