[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] A key or an event can be bound to one or more of the following actions.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] Each **transform*** action has a corresponding **bg-transform*** variant that runs the command in the background.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] Multiple actions can be chained using **+** separator.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] Any action after a terminal action that exits fzf, such as **accept** or **abort**, is ignored.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] An action denoted with **(...)** suffix takes an argument.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] If the argument contains parentheses, fzf may fail to parse the expression.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] In that case, you can use any of the following alternative notations to avoid parse errors.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] The last one is the special form that frees you from parse errors as it does not expect the closing character.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] The catch is that it should be the last one in the comma-separated list of key-action pairs.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] With **execute(...)** action, you can execute arbitrary commands without leaving fzf.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] For example, you can turn fzf into a simple file browser by binding **enter** key to **less** command like follows.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] You can use the same placeholder expressions as in **--preview**.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] fzf switches to the alternate screen when executing a command.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] However, if the command is expected to complete quickly, and you are not interested in its output, you might want to use **execute-silent** instead, which silently executes the command without the switching.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] Note that fzf will not be responsive until the command is complete.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] For asynchronous execution, start your command as a background process (i.e. appending **&**).
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] On *nix systems, fzf runs the command with **$SHELL -c** if **SHELL** is set, otherwise with **sh -c**, so in this case make sure that the command is POSIX-compliant.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] See https://github.com/junegunn/fzf/issues/1750 for more info.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] Actions with **transform-** prefix are used to transform the states of fzf using the output of an external command.
[src:fzf/man-fzf-p02] The output of these commands are expected to be a single line of text.
